\subsection{A-group}
\begin{definition}\label{group.a_group}
\uses{group.abelian,group.monomial,group.solvable,group.z_group}
An **A-group** is a group all of whose Sylow subgroups are {{ KNOWL("group.abelian", "abelian")}}. 

Every {{KNOWL('group.z_group', 'Z-group')}} is an A-group, but the converse does not hold, as shown by <a href="{{url_for('abstract.index')}}?Agroup=yes&Zgroup=no">these examples</a>.  Every {{KNOWL('group.solvable', 'solvable')}} A-group is {{KNOWL('group.monomial', 'monomial')}}.
\end{definition}


